items.title: Porcello steps up, pitches like '16 Cy winner
items.summary: The circumstances surrounding Rick Porcello all but required a big start for the Red Sox right-hander. A night earlier, Boston churned through eight relievers in a 15-inning victory over the Rays. A marathon requires a breather for its participants in its aftermath.

items.title: Bird soars with confidence, consistency intact
items.summary: Greg Bird knew there would eventually be nights like this again, but as weeks turned into months on the disabled list, there were times when the Yankees first baseman wondered how long it was going to take.

items.title: Myers exits in 6th after fouling ball off knee
items.summary: Padres first baseman Wil Myers left Saturday night's game with a right leg contusion after fouling off a ball his right knee.

items.title: River Bandits sweep Midwest League championship
items.summary: Quad Cities led from start to finish as the River Bandits completed the sweep and cruised to a Midwest League title with a 12-2 win over Fort Wayne on Saturday night.
